reviews_data.review_text: One of my favorite coffee spots. They always have a fun seasonal menu. Tried the Hay girl, Hay today and it was delicious 😋
Great coffee, friendly staff and patrons. Very cool atmosphere in walkable downtown. Come check it out!

We were exploring Kannapolis with our son, today. He only has another week before he heads back to university.
Suddenly everyone wanted coffee and I had been wanting to try Local Patriot Roasting Co. so we popped in this afternoon. I took lots of pics to show the details. I think it’s a cute space, too! I can imagine getting some work done at one of these tables. We were also impressed with the coffees! We’ll definitely come back again.

I ❤️ Coffee ☕️

Josephine Local Guide
Cute little coffee shop with a nice vibe and delicious coffee
Always closed takes 30 mins to find a parking spot downtown really sucks
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Eliseo,
We are very sorry to see this one star review. We are open 7 days a week 6:30 to 5 M-F and 8 to 5 on Saturday and Sunday. As far as parking unfortunately we do not have control over the spaces the City has provided. We wish we could provide more but it is not up to us.

reviews_data.review_text: Good coffee. Friendly staff. Cool company name.
Great coffee, and not a single tyrant in site. Just as the signers of the Declaration of Independence intended.

I was disappointed by the lack of customer service during my first visit to this establishment. Both ladies behind the counter acknowledged my presence but continued their conversation without offering any greeting. I stood there awkwardly for an unreasonably long time before anyone addressed me. Please don’t take this as a negative critique, but I do believe excellent customer service should be a top priority. On a positive note, the coffee I had was delicious, and the patriotic atmosphere was exceptional.
Best local coffee shop
Really enjoy coming here for coffee and to walk around the town. Always support your local law enforcement.

Walked in. Two employees (women). Stood at register, about 3ft in front of the person behind the counter. The other person walked behind me and behind the counter. I stood there an uncomfortable amount of time. Neither spoke or acknowledged me. Just weird and awkward. I walked out slowly, thinking one of them might say something, but nada. If you are into a strange, and unhelpful experience,  this is definitely your place! I'm a veteran by the way & there was nothing "patriot" about it.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for visiting Local Patriot! We apologize that nobody greeted you, we definitely try our best with that. It also sounds like you caught us during shift change, when the girls are restocking and today was a very busy day for us. Again our apologies.  We tend to let our customers read the menu and approach the area to order before we ask them what they would like to order. 
And of course, thank you for your service to our country. 
We hope that you will come back in and give us another try and also notice our American flag proudly flying outside of our store, our American flag framed in our store, our patch wall, our American flag pole that every visiting Veteran signs, our pay it forward board which allows for veterans and first responders to drink for free, and also our general love for our country as examples of our patriotism.

reviews_data.review_text: I drive past many other coffee places to support this business. Great coffee and great folks. 🇺🇸

I come here all the time and order the same thing,  perfect all the time. Always yummy. Perfect place to study, the tables and chairs don't rock, there is sunny/shaddy/in-between seating so it's great for any day. Most people who come in bring dogs so just be aware of that. Some of the newer girls could use some customer service skills, but that's the only time I had an issue with my order and they fixed it right away.
Overall pretty good place, gets crowded really fast so you gotta grab a seat when you find it. Proud to be a local patriot!

Love this! My husband, newborn, and I walked around town after being disappointed by another coffee place and wanted to find a location to hang and read for a bit. I got the iced Two Peeps (salted caramel and coconut) and WOW it was amazing. Cute atmosphere, friendly staff. I love that they allow dogs inside. I’ll definitely come back next time I come to town!
Took my girlfriend here for coffee on her birthday otwb from vacation and she loved it. Great atmosphere.
Took my girlfriend here for coffee on her birthday otwb from vacation and she loved it. Great atmosphere.
10/10 place! Unlike other coffee shops they have great WiFi which means I can work or study from here and enjoy the atmosphere and coffee!

Sunday morning and this place was hopping. A significant queue that never did seem to get resolved while I was here and watching.

This is a nice spot for sitting and working on laptops as there is power at each of the high top tables, the wifi worked well and the coffee is good. I'm not sure how long you can park along West Avenue but on the weekend it did not seem to be limited.

I enjoyed my drip coffee and I enjoyed writing a Yelp review or five. This was a comfy space.

I absolutely charming local coffee shop with amazing people! We had an issue there a couple of days ago and had to call the firefighters to come help. The staff was absolutely supportive and kind through the whole process. Even giving my mother a free tea. My mother, who is an absolute tea fanatic, said it was the best he ever had in her life! reviews_data.review_text: Unfortunately not that great. My husband and I have been here twice and wanted to like it but everything we’ve tried is just mediocre. Service wasn’t very friendly compared to other local places I’ve been. Also, you can’t get decaf in anything iced which is a huge bummer so we definitely won’t be returning.

The whole staff is super helpful and knowledgeable, and helped me out with the many questions I bothered them with. I really appreciate that you can purchase their syrups, as well as the fact that they have so many to choose from for your drinks. The espresso itself is pretty good, but their best qualities are their drink menu options and helpful baristas.

reviews_data.review_text: So impressed from the moment I walked in. Super cozy atmosphere and very cute decor. The staff was very friendly! What impressed me the most was when I asked for a dairy free drink and what options they had (if any), Stephanie knew right away. The lack of hesitation for something such as an allergy was very impressive. It made me feel very comfortable and I did not feel as though I was an inconvenience like I have felt at many other coffee places. I will definitely be returning and will 100% be recommending this business to family and friends! The coffee was absolutely delicious as well. 10/10, wonderful job!

reviews_data.review_text: Love a local coffee shop over commercial ones. Love the support for military and the police, but I stopped in today after my morning run, and saw a Sheriff pay for his coffee… I support all law enforcement, and hope this was an oversight by the cashier.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Joe. We have a pay it forward board behind the counter with tallies for each branch of service and our first responders where our customers have paid for them. When our service members and first responders come in they can choose to take one off of the board however if they don't always do it and pay instead. This morning our local Sheriff decided he wanted to pay for his coffee. We encourage them to take them off the board but they don't always want to.

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome for what they do for us veterans and community service members.  Coffee is pretty good, bought a bag of whole bean for home and its pretty tasty. Once I left and got up the road and started to drink the latte, it tasted like a cup of whole milk with very little Chai taste and gritty from not being mixed well.  But I'll be back, previous times have be excellent.

reviews_data.review_text: So impressed from the moment I walked in. Super cozy atmosphere and very cute decor. The staff was very friendly! What impressed me the most was when I asked for a dairy free drink and what options they had (if any), Stephanie knew right away. The lack of hesitation for something such as an allergy was very impressive. It made me feel very comfortable and I did not feel as though I was an inconvenience like I have felt at many other coffee places. I will definitely be returning and will 100% be recommending this business to family and friends! The coffee was absolutely delicious as well. 10/10, wonderful job!

reviews_data.review_text: Love a local coffee shop over commercial ones. Love the support for military and the police, but I stopped in today after my morning run, and saw a Sheriff pay for his coffee… I support all law enforcement, and hope this was an oversight by the cashier.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Joe. We have a pay it forward board behind the counter with tallies for each branch of service and our first responders where our customers have paid for them. When our service members and first responders come in they can choose to take one off of the board however if they don't always do it and pay instead. This morning our local Sheriff decided he wanted to pay for his coffee. We encourage them to take them off the board but they don't always want to.
